{"id":528,"folder_name":"045-DOW-UAP-D28-_Mission_Report-_Iraq-_September_2024","dataset_row":45,"source_title":"DOW-UAP-D28, Mission Report, Iraq, September 2024","source_url":"https://www.war.gov/medialink/ufo/release_1/dow-uap-d28-mission-report-east-china-sea-2024.pdf","thumbnail_url":"https://www.war.gov/medialink/ufo/release_1/thumbnail/dow-uap-d28-mission-report-east-china-sea-2024.jpg","pdf_local_path":null,"release_date":"2026-05-08","description_blurb":"This document is a Mission Report (MISREP), a standardized reporting form the U.S. Military uses to record the circumstances surrounding its operations. U.S. military services often use MISREPs to report Unidentified Anomalous Phenomena (UAP) to AARO. The GENTEXT, or “general text” section of these reports often contains important qualitative, contextual information, distinguishing it from the more quantitative, or numerical, data found elsewhere in the report.\nWhile conducting a weapons calibration test, U.S. military operators reported observing a lens flare via MX-20 and MX-25 IR sensors after firing an AGM-176 Griffin air-to-surface missile. The operators described the source of the flare as a UAP moving through the aircraft’s sensor’s field-of-view at a high rate of speed. The reporter assessed that the flare was associated with “a significant heat source.”\nAll descriptive and estimative language contained in this report reflects the reporter’s subjective interpretation at the time of the event. Such characterizations should not be interpreted as a conclusive indication of the presence or absence of any intrinsic object features or performance characteristics.","title":"DOW-UAP-D28, Mission Report, Iraq, September 2024","agency":"Department of War","incident_date":"2024-09-20","incident_date_min":null,"incident_date_max":null,"incident_location":"Iraq","document_type":"MISREP","summary":"U.S. military operators conducting an armed overwatch mission and weapons calibration in Iraq observed an Unidentified Aerial Phenomena (UAP) during a PGM shot. The UAP was seen as a lens flare via MX-20 and MX-25 IR sensors, moving at a high rate of speed through the aircraft's sensor field-of-view. The reporter assessed the flare was associated with a significant heat source. The report notes that descriptive language reflects subjective interpretation and not conclusive indications of object features.","reported_object_description":"lens flare, UAP, significant heat source","reported_behavior":"moving through the aircraft’s sensor’s field-of-view at a high rate of speed","official_resolution":"The observation was described as a \"lens flare\" and its source as a \"UAP\". The report emphasizes that descriptions are subjective and not conclusive, providing no definitive identification of the UAP.","bust_score":90,"bust_reasoning":"The bust score is high because the document's metadata itself provides a strong mundane explanation ('lens flare'), and the observation occurred during a PGM shot, a context highly prone to sensor artifacts or debris. The narrative is very sparse on details that would challenge these prosaic explanations, such as specific, anomalous kinematics or confirmed multi-sensor detection of an object with properties inconsistent with known craft or phenomena.","latitude":null,"longitude":null,"geocode_source":null,"full_text":"# DOW-UAP-D28, Mission Report, Iraq, September 2024 - Page 1\n\nDeclassified by MG Richard A. Harrison\nUSCENTCOM Chief of Staff\nDeclassified on: 24 October 2025\n\nSECRET//REL TO USA, FVEY\n\n# Misrep undefined-10431840\n\n## Narrative\n\n(SECRET//REL TO USA, FVEY) [redacted] DEPARTED OKAS AT 1740Z TO CONDUCT ARMED OVERWATCH IVO 38SKC[redacted] ARRIVED ON STATION AT APPROXIMATELY 1930Z AND CHECKED IN WITH [redacted]. PERFORMED A WEAPONS CALIBRATION, HAVING RELEASED 20x105mm, 101x30mm, 1xAGM-176. [redacted]'S CREW OBSERVED AN UNIDENTIFIED AERIAL PHENOMENA DURING ITS PGM SHOT (SEE UAP 1). [redacted] WAS CLEARED OFF STATION AT 2323Z. GFC INTENT MET. [redacted] LANDED AT OKAS AT 0046Z.\n\n## (S/RELIDO) Mission Narrative\n\n## Admin\n\n### CLASSIFICATION\n* **Classification:** SECRET\n* **Associated Caveats:** REL TO USA, FVEY\n* **Classification Source (MS or Classification Guide ID):** MS\n* **Declassification Date (YYYYMMDD):** 20490921\n\n### OPERATION\n* **Operation:** INHERENT RESOLVE\n* **Domain:** AIR\n* **Operations Center:** 609th\n* **Major Command (MAJCOM):** AFSOC\n* **Combatant Command (COCOM):** USCENTCOM\n\n### MSGID\n* **Report Type:** MISREP\n* **Originator (Unit or Squadron):** SOTU 016\n* **Submit Date:**\n\n***\n\n3.5c, FOIA Exemption (b)(6)\n\nSECRET//REL TO USA, FVEY\n\nUSCENTCOM MDR 25-0100 thru 25-0103 / JS-250710-TM8S  &nbsp\n\n\n\n# DOW-UAP-D28, Mission Report, Iraq, September 2024 - Page 2\n\nDeclassified by MG Richard A. Harrison\nUSCENTCOM Chief of Staff\nDeclassified on: 24 October 2025\n\nSECRET//REL TO USA, FVEY\n\n### MSNID\n* **Tasking Order (ATO):** HM\n* **Mission Type:** ARMED OVERWATCH\n* **ATO Mission Number:** [redacted] 1.4a, (b)(1)1.4g\n* **Country Tasked:** US - UNITED STATES\n* **Service Tasked:** A - AIR FORCE\n\n### Poc\n\n### POC\n* **Rank:** CAPT\n* **Full Name:** [redacted] Exemptions (b)(3), 130b, (b)(6)\n* **Unit:** 16 SOS\n* **Wing:** 27 SOW\n* **Phone Number:** [redacted] FOIA Exemption (b)(6)\n* **Email:** [redacted] 3.5c, FOIA Exemption (b)(6)\n* **Service:** Air Force\n* **Operations Center:** Other\n\n### QC\n* **Rank:** SrA\n* **Full Name:** [redacted] Exemptions (b)(3), 130b, (b)(6)\n* **Unit:** Unavailable\n* **Wing:** 1 SOW\n* **Phone Number:** [redacted] FOIA Exemption (b)(6)\n* **Email:** [redacted] 3.5c, FOIA Exemption (b)(6)\n* **Service:** Air Force\n* **Operations Center:** Other\n\n### APPROVER\n* **Rank:** SSgt\n* **Full Name:** [redacted] FOIA Exemptions (b)(3), 130b (b)(6)\n* **Unit:** ACF\n* **Wing:** 379 AEW\n* **Phone Number:** [redacted] FOIA Exemption (b)(6)\n* **Email:** [redacted] 3.5c, FOIA Exemption (b)(6)\n* **Service:** Air Force\n* **Operations Center:** 609 CAOC\n\n[redacted] 3.5c, FOIA Exemption (b)(6)\n\nSECRET//REL TO USA, FVEY\nUSCENTCOM MDR 25-0100 thru 25-0103 / JS-250710-TM8S 10/28/25 002\nApproved for Release to AARO\n\n\n\n# DOW-UAP-D28, Mission Report, Iraq, September 2024 - Page 3\n\nDeclassified by MG Richard A. Harrison\nUSCENTCOM Chief of Staff\nDeclassified on: 24 October 2025\n\nSECRET//REL TO USA, FVEY\n\n# INGEST\n\n* **Rank:**\n* **Full Name:**\n* **Unit:**\n* **Wing:**\n* **Phone Number:**\n* **Email:**\n* **Service:**\n* **Operations Center:**\n\n# ACEQUIP\n\n## ACEQUIP\n\n* **Aircraft Callsign:** [redacted]\n* **Radar Name or Destination:** AN/APN-241\n* **Radar Software Load or Mission Data:** AN/ALR-56M\n* **Radar Warning Receiver (RWR) Name or Designator:** ALR-56M\n* **RWR Software Load or Mission Data:** AAR-47\n* **MWS Name or Designator:** AAR-47\n* **MWS Software Load or Mission Data:** -\n* **IRCM Name or Designator:** AN/AAQ-24\n* **IRCM Software Load or Mission Data:** -\n* **ECM Name or Designator:** AAQ-24B\n* **ECM Software Load or Mission Data:** ALE-47\n* **CMD Name or Designator:** ALE-47\n* **Chaff Designator:** RR180\n* **Num Chaff or Cartridges:** 716\n* **Flare Designator:** MJU-71, MJU-66, M206\n* **Num Flares:** 240\n* **Towed Decoy Name or Designator:** -\n* **Towed Decoy Software Load or Mission Data:** -\n* **Num Towed Decoys:** -\n* **Type of Radar-Guided AAM:** -\n* **Num Radar-Guided AAM:** -\n* **Type of IR-Guided AAM:** -\n* **Num IR-Guided AAM:** -\n* **Gun Name or Designator:** 30MM, 105MM\n* **Num Gun Rounds:**\n* **Air-to-Ground Wpn to Include Num of Each:** 1.4(a)\n* **TGT Pod Name or Designator:** MX-25\n* **Additional Avionics:** GPS/SADL\n\n[ 3.5c, FOIA Exemption (b)(6) ]\n\nSECRET//REL TO USA, FVEY\nUSCENTCOM MDR 25-0100 thru 25-0103 / JS-250710-TM8S                                     10/28/25 003\nApproved for Release to AARO\n\n\n\n# DOW-UAP-D28, Mission Report, Iraq, September 2024 - Page 4\n\nDeclassified by MG Richard A. Harrison\nUSCENTCOM Chief of Staff\nDeclassified on: 24 October 2025\n\nSECRET//REL TO USA, FVEY\n\n* Data Link: GATEWAY (IF BOTH)\n* Gentext: 1020x30mm / 80x105mm\n\n# Timeline\n\n## Takeoff\n* Callsign: (b)(1)1.4a\n* Number of Aircraft: 1\n* Asset Type (Aircraft): (b)(1)1.4a, (b)(1)1.4g\n* Aircraft Tail Number(s): (b)(1)1.4a, (b)(1)1.4g\n* Takeoff Location (ICAO Code): OKAS\n* Takeoff Time DTG: 201740:00ZSEP24\n* Mode 3 (IFF Codes):\n* Gentext/Additional Details:\n* Mission Canceled:\n\n## Landing\n* Last Land Location (ICAO Code): OKAS\n* Last Land Time: 210046:00ZSEP24\n* Last Engine Shutdown Time: 200101:00ZSEP24\n* Total Mission Time: 7 hours 6 minutes\n* Gentext/Additional Details:\n\n## On Station\n* Time On Station DTG: 201930:00ZSEP24\n* Callsign: (b)(1)1.4a\n* JTAR Number:\n* Killbox (Location):\n* Mission Type: ARMED OVERWATCH\n* JTAC Callsign:\n* Gentext/Additional Details:\n* Did not Arrive On Station:\n\n## Off Station\n* Time Off Station DTG: 202323:00ZSEP24\n* Total Time On Station: 3 hours 53 minutes\n* Gentext/Additional Details:\n\n[3.5c, FOIA Exemption (b)(6)]\n\nSECRET//REL TO USA, FVEY\nUSCENTCOM MDR 25-0100 thru 25-0103 / JS-250710-TM8S                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           